article_id:789,category_name:Events,title_name:New Expert and Master Difficulties Are Coming Soon to All Advanced Dragon Trials!,image_path:https://dragalialost.akamaized.net/attached/information/images/53a93677440ef70c9d113eb2a8012735.png,message:<div>A new Expert difficulty will be added to all Advanced Dragon Trials at <span class="local_date" data-local_date="1570773600"></span>!</div><div>Then, an even more challenging Master difficulty will be added on a rotating basis starting <span class="local_date" data-local_date="1571032800"></span>!</div><div>ãƒ»The Advanced Dragon Trials quests that have been available up until now will be referred to as Standard difficulty.</div><div><br></div><div><img src="https://dragalialost.akamaized.net/attached/information/images/53a93677440ef70c9d113eb2a8012735.png"></div><div><br></div><div>Notes:</div><div>1. In order to challenge Expert difficulty for each Advanced Dragon Trials quest, a player&#39;s team must have 20,000 might or higher.</div><div>2. In order to challenge Master difficulty for each Advanced Dragon Trials quest, a player&#39;s team must have 24,000 might or higher.</div><div>3. Players must have completed Standard difficulty for the corresponding Advanced Dragon Trials quest to challenge the Expert and Master difficulties.</div><div>Example: To challenge High Midgardsormr&#39;s Trial on Expert difficulty, players must clear High Midgardsormr&#39;s Trial on Standard difficulty.</div><div>4. Players must have completed up to Chapter 2 / 2-1 (Normal) of the main campaign in order to play co-op.</div><div><br></div><div>Thank you for playing Dragalia Lost.</div>,start_time:1570428000,update_time1570160309